// The `store` device's implementation: it defines the shared `Node` shape (a shape is global
// vocabulary, defined here, not in the datasheet) and a system over it. The device owns NO storage —
// the driver sizes the pool (>= the datasheet minimum) and runs this system. Support file.
// RUN: true
Node :: arche { key, val }

bump :: sys (val) {
  val = val + 1.0;
}
